picked: Millie Bobby Brown portrays Eleven (also known as "El") on the Netflix television series Stranger Things. She was born on February 19, 2004 in Marbella, Spain to British parents Kelly and Robert Brown, who are both dancers. Her family moved to Orlando, Florida when she was two years old so that her parents could pursue dancing opportunities there. After spending a few years living in Orlando and starting dance training herself, they returned to England before moving again to Los Angeles for another attempt at breaking into show business. There, she began taking acting classes with a youth program called the Party Brats, which led to initial commercial modeling work leading up to being cast in Stranger Things after reading lines from another actress audition tape.
